ual_commit_hooks.go`**\\n\\n#### `PrepareCommitMsg()` (Lines 233-388)\\n- **Lines 285-296**: **FAST PATH for ACTIVE sessions with NO TTY** (agents committing)\\n  - Calls `addTrailerForAgentCommit()` which adds checkpoint trailer **unconditionally**\\n  - **SKIPS content detection entirely**\\n  - This is the fast path used by OpenCode during interactive sessions\\n\\n#### `PostCommit()` (Lines 623-731)\\n- Called after commit is created\\n- **Lines 642-649**: Checks for checkpoint trailer in commit message\\n  - If no trailer → silently updates `BaseCommit` only (no condensation)\\n  - If trailer exists → proceeds to condensation\\n\\n#### `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` (Lines 576-603) - Within `postCommitActionHandler`\\n- **Lines 597-602**: Calls `filesOverlapWithContent()` to verify commit files match shadow branch\\n- **Critical line 588-591**: Only checks files in `committedFileSet` (files actually changed in this commit)\\n- Filters `filesTouchedBefore` to intersection with committed files before overlap check\\n\\n#### `sessionHasNewContent()` (Lines 1038-1166)\\n- Checks if session has new content beyond last checkpoint\\n- **Lines 1143-1153**: For PrepareCommitMsg, calls `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent()` with content-aware check\\n- **Lines 1128-1165**: For PostCommit (no staged files), returns transcript growth status\\n\\n#### `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript()` (Lines 1281-1378)\\n- **Lines 1316-1339**: Claude Code gets special handling with `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` for subagents\\n- **Lines 1340-1350**: **ALL OTHER AGENTS (OpenCode, Gemini, etc.) use only `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()`**\\n- Does NOT handle subagent transcripts for OpenCode!\\n\\n### 3. **File Extraction: `/Users/robin/Developer/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/transcript.go`**\\n\\n#### `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()` (Lines 92-129)\\n- **Lines 108-128**: Iterates through messages starting at `startOffset`\\n- Extracts files from assistant messages with tool call